## Verdict: PASS

No new findings from static inspection.

## Addressed

- Finding 1 closed. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:3024), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs:398)  
  `probe_wal_sidecar()` now opens the sidecar and `read_exact`s a `[u8; 32]`, so the engine-side probe is bounded to the WAL header only. The new 256 MiB sparse-WAL test is only wall-clock signal, not a byte-counter proof, but it is an acceptable fallback per the remediation spec and is strong enough to catch regression back to `std::fs::read`.

- Finding 2 closed. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs:61), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs:152), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs:216)  
  The victim writes a sentinel only after the first `engine.write()` returns, the parent waits for that sentinel before sampling the kill delay, and sentinel miss is surfaced as a hard panic after sending `SIGKILL`. `lost_commit_ms` is now mandatory and p99 is computed across the full `P_PWR_TRIALS` set.

- Finding 3 closed. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs:272), [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_open_path.rs:363)  
  AC-035c now spawns `Command::new(current_exe())` with an env-gated `_lock_acquire_probe_entry`, so the lock probe runs in a distinct OS process, not another fd in the same process. The old in-process reacquire remains only as extra sanity signal.

- Finding 4 closed. Refs: [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs:292)  
  `ac_034c_os_crash_zero_committed_tx_loss()` now `panic!()`s with actionable substrate-gap text and pointers to the missing VM/sysrq fixture. Clearing `#[ignore]` without implementing the harness now fails loudly.

- No regression is evident in AC-035a/b from the deltas. Those assertions remain intact, and the remediation commits only add the bounded-read test plus the sibling-process probe around the existing open-path matrix. The available runtime artifact, [dev/plans/runs/12-D-fix-1-output.json](/tmp/fdb-12-D-durability-harnesses-20260517T185755Z/dev/plans/runs/12-D-fix-1-output.json:1), reports `durability_open_path` passed, `error_taxonomy` passed, and `agent-verify` passed.

